#. <section class="sutta" id="sn41.5"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn41.5:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 41"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 41"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn41.5:0.2"
msgid "1. Cittavagga"
msgstr "1. With Citta"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn41.5:0.3"
msgid "5. Paṭhamakāmabhūsutta"
msgstr "5. With Kāmabhū (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn41.5:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā kāmabhū macchikāsaṇḍe viharati ambāṭakavane."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Kāmabhū was staying near Macchikāsaṇḍa in the Wild "
"Mango Grove."

msgctxt "sn41.5:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho citto gahapati yenāyasmā kāmabhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmantaṃ kāmabhuṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho "
"cittaṃ gahapatiṃ āyasmā kāmabhū etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Citta the householder went up to Venerable Kāmabhū, bowed, and sat down "
"to one side. Kāmabhū said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn41.5:2.1"
msgid "“Vuttamidaṃ, gahapati:"
msgstr "“Householder, there is this saying:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn41.5:3.1"
msgid "‘Nelaṅgo setapacchādo,"
msgstr "‘With flawless wheel and white canopy,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn41.5:3.2"
msgid "ekāro vattatī ratho;"
msgstr "the one-spoke chariot rolls on."

#. <br>
#. VAR: āyantaṃ → appattaṃ (s1, s2, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn41.5:3.3"
msgid "Anīghaṃ passa āyantaṃ,"
msgstr "See it come, untroubled,"

# I’m unconvinced by chinnasota here, it just seems like such a mixed metaphor. Thag 4.4 has chinnasutta abandhana, which is at least more consistent. However, if it is a mistake, it is an old one, for the Chinese at SA 566 supports sota: 斷流不復縛.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn41.5:3.4"
msgid "chinnasotaṃ abandhanan’ti."
msgstr "with stream cut, unbound.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn41.5:4.1"
msgid ""
"Imassa nu kho, gahapati, saṅkhittena bhāsitassa kathaṃ vitthārena attho "
"daṭṭhabbo”ti?"
msgstr "How should we see the detailed meaning of this brief statement?”"

msgctxt "sn41.5:4.2"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho etaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā bhāsitan”ti?"
msgstr "“Sir, was this spoken by the Buddha?”"

msgctxt "sn41.5:4.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, gahapatī”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, householder.”"

msgctxt "sn41.5:4.4"
msgid "“Tena hi, bhante, muhuttaṃ āgamehi yāvassa atthaṃ pekkhāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, sir, please wait a moment while I consider the meaning of this.”"

msgctxt "sn41.5:4.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho citto gahapati muhuttaṃ tuṇhī hutvā āyasmantaṃ kāmabhuṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then after a short silence Citta said to Kāmabhū:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.292"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn41.5:5.1"
msgid "“‘Nelaṅgan’ti kho, bhante, sīlānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "“Sir, ‘flawless wheel’ is a term for ethics."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.2"
msgid "‘Setapacchādo’ti kho, bhante, vimuttiyā etaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘White canopy’ is a term for freedom."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.3"
msgid "‘Ekāro’ti kho, bhante, satiyā etaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘One spoke’ is a term for mindfulness."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.4"
msgid "‘Vattatī’ti kho, bhante, abhikkamapaṭikkamassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘Rolls on’ is a term for going forward and coming back."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.5"
msgid ""
"‘Ratho’ti kho, bhante, imassetaṃ cātumahābhūtikassa kāyassa adhivacanaṃ "
"mātāpettikasambhavassa odanakummāsūpacayassa "
"aniccucchādanaparimaddanabhedanaviddhaṃsanadhammassa."
msgstr ""
"‘Chariot’ is a term for this body made up of the four primary elements, "
"produced by mother and father, built up from rice and porridge, liable to "
"impermanence, to wearing away and erosion, to breaking up and destruction."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.6"
msgid "Rāgo kho, bhante, nīgho, doso nīgho, moho nīgho."
msgstr "Greed, hate, and delusion are troubles."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.7"
msgid ""
"Te khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā "
"āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant who has ended the defilements has given these up, cut them off "
"at the root, made them like a palm stump, and obliterated them, so they are "
"unable to arise in the future."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.8"
msgid "Tasmā khīṇāsavo bhikkhu ‘anīgho’ti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"That’s why a mendicant who has ended the defilements is called ‘untroubled’."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.9"
msgid "‘Āyantan’ti kho, bhante, arahato etaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘The one who comes’ is a term for the perfected one."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.10"
msgid "‘Soto’ti kho, bhante, taṇhāyetaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘Stream’ is a term for craving."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.11"
msgid ""
"Sā khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā "
"āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant who has ended the defilements has given this up, cut it off at "
"the root, made it like a palm stump, and obliterated it, so it’s unable to "
"arise in the future."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.12"
msgid "Tasmā khīṇāsavo bhikkhu ‘chinnasoto’ti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"That’s why a mendicant who has ended the defilements is said to have ‘cut "
"the stream’."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.13"
msgid "Rāgo kho, bhante, bandhanaṃ, doso bandhanaṃ, moho bandhanaṃ."
msgstr "Greed, hate, and delusion are bonds."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.14"
msgid ""
"Te khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā "
"āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant who has ended the defilements has given these up, cut them off "
"at the root, made them like a palm stump, and obliterated them, so they are "
"unable to arise in the future."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.15"
msgid "Tasmā khīṇāsavo bhikkhu ‘abandhano’ti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"That’s why a mendicant who has ended the defilements is called ‘unbound’."

msgctxt "sn41.5:5.16"
msgid "Iti kho, bhante, yaṃ taṃ bhagavatā vuttaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"So, sir, that’s how I understand the detailed meaning of what the Buddha "
"said in brief:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn41.5:6.1"
msgid "‘Nelaṅgo setapacchādo,"
msgstr "‘With flawless wheel and white canopy,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn41.5:6.2"
msgid "ekāro vattatī ratho;"
msgstr "the one-spoke chariot rolls on."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn41.5:6.3"
msgid "Anīghaṃ passa āyantaṃ,"
msgstr "See it come, untroubled,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn41.5:6.4"
msgid "chinnasotaṃ abandhanan’ti."
msgstr "with stream cut, unbound.’”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn41.5:7.1"
msgid ""
"Imassa kho, bhante, bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ "
"ājānāmī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn41.5:7.2"
msgid "“Lābhā te, gahapati, suladdhaṃ te, gahapati."
msgstr "“You’re fortunate, householder, so very fortunate,"

msgctxt "sn41.5:7.3"
msgid "Yassa te gambhīre buddhavacane paññācakkhu kamatī”ti."
msgstr "to traverse the Buddha’s deep teachings with the eye of wisdom.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn41.5:7.4"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
